Local Git Setup Commands (in VS Code Terminal):
# 1. Initialize Git in your folder
git init

# 2. Add all files to staging (ready to be committed)
git add .

# 3. Commit the files with a message
git commit -m "first commit"


Connect to GitHub & Push Code
# 4. Connect your local folder to your GitHub repo (replace the URL with your own)
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git

# 5. Push the code to GitHub (first time)
git push -u origin master

3 commands to update GitHub:
git add .
git commit -m "your new message"
git push
